</lyxtabular>

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Physical interpretation:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The mean reflects the center of mass of the particle plume.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The mode reflects the most probable arrival time,
 which is more sensitive to early or delayed arrivals due to dispersion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When the mean velocity remains constant confirms a linear advecton front.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The the mode shifts sublinearly with distance implies that the spread (dispersion) becomes more significant with distance,
 skewing the distributioin more and pushing the peak back.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The median is the time at which the cdf=0.5 as half the particles take shorter and the other half longer than this time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The mean velocity is equal to the surface to the left of the cdf.
 This too is obvious.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The model is the time at which the cdf is steepest,
 i.e.
 its first derivative peaks (this is obviously the top of the pdf).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An easy and informative criterion for early and late arrivals may be built on 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathtt{loc}$
\end_inset

 as the earlies possible moment of arrival of particles and 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{mode}$
\end_inset

 as the most probable time of arrival.
 We may select point based on the ratio of these two times.
 Let's,
 just for convenience rename 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathtt{loc}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
t_{0}=\mathtt{loc}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
then we can base arrival time criteria on the ratio
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\alpha=\frac{t-t_{0}}{t_{mode}-t_{0}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
and so
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
t=t_{0}+\left(t_{mode}-t_{0}\right)\alpha
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
and use the following arrival criteria
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float table
placement document
alignment document
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Arrival criteria
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

